g401.definition: [ἀνάχυσις] from a comparative of {{g303}} and χέω (to pour); properly, effusion, i.e. (figuratively) license

g403.definition: [ἀνάψυξις] from {{g404}}; properly, a recovery of breath, i.e. (figuratively) revival

g404.definition: [ἀναψύχω] from {{g303}} and {{g5594}}; properly, to cool off, i.e. (figuratively) relieve

g405.definition: [ἀνδραποδιστής] from a derivative of a compound of {{g435}} and {{g4228}}; an enslaver (as bringing men to his feet)

g407.definition: [ἀνδρίζομαι] middle voice from {{g435}}; to act manly

g408.definition: [Ἀνδρόνικος] from {{g435}} and {{g3534}}; man of victory; Andronicos, an Israelite

g410.definition: [ἀνέγκλητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g1458}}; unaccused, i.e. (by implication) irreproachable

g411.definition: [ἀνεκδιήγητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g1555}}; not expounded in full, i.e. indescribable

g412.definition: [ἀνεκλάλητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g1583}}; not spoken out, i.e. (by implication) unutterable

g413.definition: [ἀνέκλειπτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g1587}}; not left out, i.e. (by implication) inexhaustible

g414.definition: [ἀνεκτότερος] comparative of a derivative of {{g430}}; more endurable

g415.definition: [ἀνελεήμων] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g1655}}; merciless

g416.definition: [ἀνεμίζω] from {{g417}}; to toss with the wind

g417.definition: [ἄνεμος] from the base of {{g109}}; wind; (plural) by implication, (the four) quarters (of the earth)

g418.definition: [ἀνένδεκτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of the same as {{g1735}}; unadmitted, i.e. (by implication) not supposable

g419.definition: [ἀνεξερεύνητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g1830}}; not searched out, i.e. (by implication) inscrutable

g420.definition: [ἀνεξίκακος] from {{g430}} and {{g2556}}; enduring of ill, i.e. forbearing

g421.definition: [ἀνεξιχνίαστος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of a compound of {{g1537}} and a derivative of {{g2487}}; not tracked out, i.e. (by implication) untraceable

g422.definition: [ἀνεπαίσχυντος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of a compound of {{g1909}} and {{g153}}; not ashamed, i.e. irreprehensible:

g423.definition: [ἀνεπίληπτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g1949}}; not arrested, i.e. (by implication) inculpable

g426.definition: [ἀνετάζω] from {{g303}} and ἐτάζω (to test); to investigate (judicially)

g428.definition: [ἀνεύθετος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2111}}; not well set, i.e. inconvenient

g430.definition: [ἀνέχομαι] middle voice from {{g303}} and {{g2192}}; to hold oneself up against, i.e. (figuratively) put up with

g431.definition: [ἀνεψιός] from {{g1}} (as a particle of union) and an obsolete νέπος (a brood); properly, akin, i.e. (specially) a cousin

g433.definition: [ἀνήκω] from {{g303}} and {{g2240}}; to attain to, i.e. (figuratively) be proper

g434.definition: [ἀνήμερος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and ἥμερος (lame); savage

g435.definition: [ἀνήρ] a primary word (compare {{g444}}); a man (properly as an individual male)

g436.definition: [ἀνθίστημι] from {{g473}} and {{g2476}}; to stand against, i.e. oppose

g437.definition: [ἀνθομολογέομαι] from {{g473}} and the middle voice of {{g3670}}; to confess in turn, i.e. respond in praise

g439.definition: [ἀνθρακιά] from {{g440}}; a bed of burning coals

g440.definition: [ἄνθραξ] of uncertain derivation; a live coal

g443.definition: [ἀνθρωποκτόνος] from {{g444}} and κτείνω(to kill); a manslayer Compare {{g5406}}.

g444.definition: [ἄνθρωπος] from {{g435}} and ὤψ (the countenance; from {{g3700}}); man-faced, i.e. a human being

g446.definition: [ἀνθύπατος] from {{g473}} and a superlative of {{g5228}}; instead of the highest officer, i.e. (specially) a Roman proconsul

g447.definition: [ἀνίημι] from {{g303}} and ἵημι (to send); to let up, i.e. (literally) slacken or (figuratively) desert, desist from

g448.definition: [ἀνίλεως] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2436}}; inexorable

g449.definition: [ἄνιπτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g3538}}; without ablution

g450.definition: [ἀνίστημι] from {{g303}} and {{g2476}}; to stand up (literal or figurative, transitive or intransitive)

g451.definition: [Ἄννα] of Hebrew origin ({{h2584}}); Anna, an Israelitess

g452.definition: [Ἄννας] of Hebrew origin ({{h2608}}); Annas (i.e. {{g367}}), an Israelite

g453.definition: [ἀνόητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g3539}}; unintelligent; by implication, sensual

g454.definition: [ἄνοια] from a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3563}}; stupidity; by implication, rage

g455.definition: [ἀνοίγω] from {{g303}} and οἴγω (to open); to open up (literally or figuratively, in various applications)

g458.definition: [ἀνομία] from {{g459}}; illegality, i.e. violation of law or (genitive case) wickedness

g459.definition: [ἄνομος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3551}}; lawless, i.e. (negatively) not subject to (the Jewish) law; (by implication, a Gentile), or (positively) wicked

g460.definition: [ἀνόμως] adverb from {{g459}}; lawlessly, i.e. (specially) not amenable to (the Jewish) law

g461.definition: [ἀνορθόω] from {{g303}} and a derivative of the base of {{g3717}}; to straighten up

g462.definition: [ἀνόσιος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3741}}; wicked

g465.definition: [ἀντάλλαγμα] from a compound of {{g473}} and {{g236}}; an equivalent or ransom

g467.definition: [ἀνταποδίδωμι] from {{g473}} and {{g591}}; to requite (good or evil)

g470.definition: [ἀνταποκρίνομαι] from {{g473}} and {{g611}}; to contradict or dispute

g471.definition: [ἀντέπω] from {{g473}} and {{g2036}}; to refute or deny

g472.definition: [ἀντέχομαι] from {{g473}} and the middle voice of {{g2192}}; to hold oneself opposite to, i.e. (by implication) adhere to; by extension to care for

g473.definition: [ἀντί] a primary particle; opposite, i.e. instead or because of (rarely in addition to) Often used in composition to denote contrast, requital, substitution, correspondence, etc.

g475.definition: [ἀντιδιατίθεμαι] from {{g473}} and {{g1303}}; to set oneself opposite, i.e. be  disputatious

g476.definition: [ἀντίδικος] from {{g473}} and {{g1349}}; an opponent (in a lawsuit); specially, Satan (as the arch-enemy)

g477.definition: [ἀντίθεσις] from a compound of {{g473}} and {{g5087}}; opposition, i.e. a conflict (of theories)

g478.definition: [ἀντικαθίστημι] from {{g473}} and {{g2525}}; to set down (troops) against, i.e. withstand

g479.definition: [ἀντικαλέω] from {{g473}} and {{g2564}}; to invite in return

g480.definition: [ἀντίκειμαι] from {{g473}} and {{g2749}}; to lie opposite, i.e. be adverse (figuratively, repugnant) to

g482.definition: [ἀντιλαμβάνομαι] from {{g473}} and the middle voice of {{g2983}}; to take hold of in turn, i.e. succor; also to participate

g485.definition: [ἀντιλογία] from a derivative of {{g483}}; dispute, disobedience

g486.definition: [ἀντιλοιδορέω] from {{g473}} and {{g3058}}; to rail in reply

g488.definition: [ἀντιμετρέω] from {{g473}} and {{g3354}}; to mete in return

g489.definition: [ἀντιμισθία] from a compound of {{g473}} and {{g3408}}; requital, correspondence

g490.definition: [Ἀντιόχεια] from Ἀντίοχυς (a Syrian king); Antiochia, a place in Syria

g491.definition: [Ἀντιοχεύς] from {{g490}}; an Antiochian or inhabitant of Antiochia

g492.definition: [ἀντιπαρέρχομαι] from {{g473}} and {{g3928}}; to go along opposite

g493.definition: [Ἀντίπας] contracted for a compound of {{g473}} and a derivative of {{g3962}}; Antipas, a Christian

g494.definition: [Ἀντιπατρίς] from the same as {{g493}}; Antipatris, a place in Palestine

g495.definition: [ἀντιπέραν] from {{g473}} and {{g4008}}; on the opposite side

g496.definition: [ἀντιπίπτω] from {{g473}} and {{g4098}} (including its alternate); to oppose

g497.definition: [ἀντιστρατεύομαι] from {{g473}} and {{g4754}}; (figuratively) to attack, i.e. (by implication) destroy

g498.definition: [ἀντιτάσσομαι] from {{g473}} and the middle voice of {{g5021}}; to range oneself against, i.e. oppose

g499.definition: [ἀντίτυπον] neuter of a compound of {{g473}} and {{g5179}}; corresponding ("antitype"), i.e. a representative, counterpart

g500.definition: [ἀντίχριστος] from {{g473}} and {{g5547}}; an opponent of the Messiah
